  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PORT AGENCY OPERATIONS EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Effectively respond to assigned port calls from Pre-Arrival info messages to FDA closure.</li><li>Submission of ICA applications, Pilotage booking, transmission messages, and MPA Digiport.</li><li>Selection of contractors for goods and services provided to principals, including submission of competitive quotations, as required.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Ships Agency processes, standards, and procedures, including correct use of the operating system.</li><li>Monitoring of the vessel and attendance to any follow-up inquiries with proactive, efficient, and timely communication at all times.</li><li>Ensure accurate PDA is created and submitted. Ensure the correct amount of pre-funding is received or the correct level of authority has approved any deviation, prior to performing the Port Call.</li><li>Establish and maintain vessel files and ensure that all transactional systems are updated in real-time.</li><li>Proactively follow up, check, and approve supplier’s invoices & record expenses that arise during vessels’ port calls.</li><li>Ensure cost effective Vessel Operation.</li><li>Ensure a consistently high level of accuracy of deliverables.</li><li>Accountable to maintain the QHSSE standard</li></ul><p><u><strong>Salary:</strong></u></p><ul><li><strong>The salary for this position is between $3,000 and $3,500, based on relevant experience, plus vessel allowances.</strong></li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least 2 years of relevant experience is required</li><li>Proficient in English (written and spoken).</li><li>HIGHER NITEC / Diploma in Maritime Studies or equivalent</li><li>Good language, interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Positive attitude, willingness to learn</li><li>Ability to work independently as we well as part of a team</li><li>Ability to work under pressure, multi-task and meet tight deadlines</li><li>Basic proficiency with IT applications</li></ul>",
